Unfortunately, the party district organizations remain loyal to Hugenberg, who has worked to fill the party bureaucracy with his own supporters. As a result, the defection of the entire moderate wing of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> is less impactful than it would have been. Furthermore, many on the right believe that an internal resolution is not a strong enough pretext to break with the party and may choose to remain with Hugenberg.